The core idea remains the same: identify if an array is completely sorted (ascending or descending) in $O(N)$ time and only apply the $O(N \log N)$ `std::sort` if it is not. 

However, instead of writing stateful manual loops with variables tracking our direction, we can use `std::is_sorted_until`.
